Note on third-party data:

The codebase consumes several public datasets, each with its own licence.
Bulk observational data is fetched by the pipeline at run time and is not
redistributed in this repository; two small derived boundary/geology files
are committed with provenance notes (see their .source.json files). Use of
all sources is governed by their own terms:

  - EA Hydrology API readings              — Open Government Licence v3.0
  - EA Flood-Monitoring API                — Open Government Licence v3.0
  - EA Aquifer Designation (Bedrock)       — Open Government Licence v3.0
    (committed: data/geology/aquifer_bedrock.geojson, OGL v3.0,
     contains Environment Agency information © Environment Agency and/or
     database right)
  - ONS Countries (December 2024) Boundaries UK BUC
    (committed: data/regions/england_wales.geojson, OGL v3.0,
     Source: Office for National Statistics licensed under the Open
     Government Licence v3.0; contains OS data © Crown copyright and
     database right 2024)
  - ECMWF Open Data (ENS forecasts)        — CC BY 4.0, © ECMWF
  - Open-Meteo API (forecast + ERA5 archive transport)
                                           — free tier: non-commercial use
     only (CC BY-NC 4.0); commercial use requires an Open-Meteo API
     subscription (set GWC_OPEN_METEO_API_KEY). ERA5 data © ECMWF /
     Copernicus Climate Change Service.

GroundwaterCast UK is an independent open-source project. It is not
affiliated with, or endorsed by, the Environment Agency, the Office for
National Statistics, ECMWF, Open-Meteo, or any water company.
